cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it presents a cooperative medium access control (MAC) protocol designed for distributed wireless networks. It also discusses a relay selection mechanism for optimal relay selection depending on channel conditions. 

It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses increasing the sum-rate of cooperative transmission by allowing packets from two selected nodes to interfere only when the desired packets can be decoded at the appropriate destinations. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as it discusses throughput and delay in the simulation results. 

It could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it presents a protocol that enables distributed, uncoordinated, and adaptive operation. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses controlling and coordinating interfering transmissions in a cooperative manner.
